<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta content='text/html; charset=UTF-8' http-equiv='Content-Type' />
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="display: block;
  max-width:130px;
  max-height:65px;
  width: auto;
  height: auto;"><%=image_tag attachments["stop-trump.png"].url%>
  <h1><%= @salutation %></h1>
    <h2> <%= @message_text %></h2>

    <h3> <table cellpadding="5" cellspacing="5">
      <tr>
      <th>Name</th>
      <th>Phone</th>
      <th>Email Link</th>
      </tr>
      <% @action_array[1,@action_array.length-1].each do |r| %>
          <tr>
          <td><%= r[:rep_name] %></td>
          <td><%= r[:rep_phone] %></td>
          <% if r[:rep_email].nil? %>
              <td>Email Not Available</td>
          <% else %>
              <td><%= link_to "Click to Send an Email Message", r[:rep_email] %></td>
          <% end  %>
          </tr>
      <% end %>
      </table>
    </h3>
    <br>
    <h2>
      <% if @zipPlus4 != "Error"%>
      Just so you know, you can't email your congressional representatives directly. You have to fill out a form on their site and send it that way. Many reps ask for your zipcode+4 before you can submit the form. Yours is <%= @zipPlus4 %>.
      <% end %>
    </h2>
    <br>
    <h3>
      <%=link_to "Unsubscribe", @base_url.to_s + "/targets/" + @target_id.to_s + "/unsubscribe", style: "border-style: solid; border-color: black; padding: 12px 18px 12px 18px; -webkit-border-radius:3px; border-radius:3px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; color: black; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block;" %>
    </h3>
  </body>
</html>
